---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { SITE } from '../config/site';
const updated = '2026-06-18';
---
<BaseLayout
  title={`Terms | ${SITE.name}`}
  description="Terms of use for the Aheadcount prototype and beta sign-up."
>
  <article class="section">
    <div class="container-x prose prose-slate max-w-3xl">
      <h1>Terms of use</h1>
      <p><em>Last updated: {updated}</em></p>

      <h2>1. Prototype status</h2>
      <p>
        {SITE.name} is an early-stage prototype offered for evaluation. Features, pricing and availability may change,
        and paid plans are not yet live — the prices shown are indicative and subject to change before launch.
      </p>

      <h2>2. The planner is guidance, not advice</h2>
      <p>
        The planner produces planning estimates from the numbers you enter, using a transparent model. It is a decision-support
        aid, not professional, financial, legal or employment advice. Forecasts are planning ranges, not guarantees of demand,
        cost, or labor availability. You are responsible for your own staffing and hiring decisions.
      </p>

      <h2>3. Beta sign-up</h2>
      <p>
        Joining the beta list means we may email you about the product. You can unsubscribe at any time. We don't sell or
        rent your data — see our <a href="/privacy/">privacy policy</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>4. Acceptable use</h2>
      <p>
        Don't misuse the site (no attempts to disrupt, reverse-engineer for harm, or scrape at scale). The site and its
        content are provided "as is", without warranties, to the extent permitted by law.
      </p>

      <h2>5. Liability</h2>
      <p>
        To the maximum extent permitted by law, {SITE.name} is not liable for any loss arising from decisions made using
        the prototype or its outputs.
      </p>

      <h2>6. Contact</h2>
      <p>Questions about these terms? Email <a href={`mailto:${SITE.contactEmail}`}>{SITE.contactEmail}</a>.</p>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
